\"Gazelle Arroyo Elite c5\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.16.18-PM.png 2362w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.16.18-PM-297x134.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.16.18-PM-800x362.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.16.18-PM-120x54.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.16.18-PM-768x348.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.16.18-PM-1536x695.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.16.18-PM-2048x927.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM.png\"><img width=\"2376\" height=\"1036\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM.png\" alt=\"Gazelle Avignon C380\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM.png 2376w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM-297x130.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM-800x349.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM-120x52.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM-768x335.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM-1536x670.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Screenshot-2023-04-18-at-6.15.41-PM-2048x893.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Product names are a bit of a mouthful. There’s the Avignon C380 HMB, the Arroyo C5, the Ultimate C380, and Ultimate T10. MSRPs check in at varying price points from $3,999 to $4,999. They’re all on step-through frames with the Avignon featuring Gazelle’s “most accessible frame to date”, though the Ultimate T10 has an optional frame with a top tube.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Avignon C380, Ultimate C380 and Ultimate T10 will be available this month through Gazelle’s network of authorized dealers across the US and Canada. The Arroyo C5 is expected around late May, 2023.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.gazellebikes.com/en-us/new-models-preview\" target=\"_blank\">gazellebikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-2023-gazelle-ebikes/\">Set it and Forget it With Gazelle eBikes’ Automatic Gearing</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Sam Anderson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8ef057f377a396732c834152743d6557fac2c8b2161e590f5156835ffca0c0c6","category":"Cycling"}